## Frequently asked questions

**Where is my data stored?**
Everything you enter — listings, commissions, leads, and notes — is stored only on
your device. Nothing is uploaded to us. Back up anytime in **Settings → Backup & Export**.

**How do I move my data to a new phone?**
On your old phone, go to **Settings → Backup & Export** and export a backup file to
iCloud Drive or Files. On the new phone, install the app and use **Import** to restore it.

**How do I export my listings and leads to a spreadsheet?**
**Settings → Backup & Export → Export CSV.** You can open the file in Numbers or Excel.

**The commission numbers — are they exact?**
All commission, tax, and net figures are **estimates for planning only** and are not
financial, legal, or tax advice. Set your splits in **Settings** so estimates match
your brokerage.

**How does the "capped" status work?**
The app totals the brokerage split from your **completed** deals. Once that reaches
your annual cap (set in Settings), it stops deducting the brokerage's cut automatically.

**How do I turn off ads / change tracking?**
Ads help keep the app free. You can change ad tracking anytime in
**iOS Settings → Privacy & Security → Tracking**.

**How do I delete my data?**
Because your data lives only on your device, deleting the app removes it. Export a
backup first if you want to keep a copy.

